# Data licensing

Every data source has a license. Adapters MUST respect it at runtime, and `docs/data-license.md` MUST be updated before merging.

## In-scope sources (Phase 0вҖ“5)

| Source | License | Redistribution | Caching | Attribution |
|---|---|---|---|---|
| Open-Meteo | CC-BY 4.0 | Allowed | 1 hour cache | "Weather data by Open-Meteo.com (CC-BY 4.0)" in tool output |
| eMAFF Fude | Public open data | Allowed (snapshot built locally; not bundled in npm package) | OK | "Source: иҫІжһ—ж°ҙз”ЈзңҒ eMAFF зӯҶгғқгғӘгӮҙгғі" |
| FAMIC pesticide | Public open data | Allowed | OK | "Source: FAMIC иҫІи–¬зҷ»йҢІжғ…е ұ" |
| JMA disaster XML | Japan Meteorological Business Act | Conditional | Short cache only (вүӨ10 min) | "ж°—иұЎеәҒ + зҷәиЎЁжҷӮеҲ» + ж”№еӨүжңүз„Ў" |

## Out-of-scope sources

- WAGRI вҖ” member agreement, **redistribution prohibited**, only allowed via Phase 7+ adapter that reads tokens from the user's own account. Do not commit any WAGRI sample data to this repo.
- Sentinel-2 / SAGRI вҖ” out of scope for this OSS release.

## Adapter contract

- Every adapter returns an `attribution: string` field in its result type.
- The tool layer copies `attribution` into `structuredContent.attribution` so the LLM can quote it.
- The MCP Apps UI shows the attribution near the data it represents.

## When you add a data source

1. Confirm license in writing.
2. Add the row to `docs/data-license.md`.
3. Add the entry to `.well-known/mcp-server.json` `data_sources`.
4. Implement the adapter with `attribution` populated.
5. Add a unit test that the attribution is non-empty.

PRs missing any of the four steps will be closed.
